01:41:16,380 --> 01:41:22,140
Bates grabbed a consensus image, drew highlights and a conclusion around the front end. Scramjet.

1109
01:41:23,340 --> 01:41:29,020
We tracked nearly 400,000 in less than two days. That appeared to be most of them.

1110
01:41:29,020 --> 01:41:33,820
New sightings leveled off afterwards. The cumulative curve flattening towards some

1111
01:41:33,820 --> 01:41:39,580
theoretical asymptote. Most of the orbits were close and fast, but Sadasti projected a frequency

1112
01:41:39,580 --> 01:41:44,700
distribution extending almost back to Pluto. We might stay out here for years and still catch

1113
01:41:44,700 --> 01:41:48,540
