01:42:38,140 --> 01:42:43,100
head was insufficient to contain them. Tactical graphics lit him from all sides, turned his

1125
01:42:43,100 --> 01:42:47,420
body into a bright patchwork of flickering tattoos. The illustrated man.

1126
01:42:48,460 --> 01:42:53,500
Mind if I come in? I asked. He grunted. Yeah, but not enough to push it.

1127
01:42:54,540 --> 01:42:58,860
Inside the dome, the sound of heavy rainfall hissed and spat behind the screeching that had

1128
01:42:58,860 --> 01:43:05,180
led me there. What is that? Ben's magnetosphere. He didn't look back. Nice, eh?

1129
01:43:06,060 --> 01:43:11,420
Synthesis didn't have opinions on the job. It keeps observers, observer effects to a minimum.

1130
01:43:12,220 --> 01:43:17,100
This time, I permitted myself a small breach. The static's nice. I could do without the screeching.

1131
01:43:17,660 --> 01:43:21,980
Are you kidding me? That's the music of the sphere, his connoisseur. It's beautiful. Like

1132
01:43:21,980 --> 01:43:28,620
