4492
06:47:14,300 --> 06:47:21,180
Pretty radical transformation though. Not these days. Didn't it change you? His body dragged on

4493
06:47:21,180 --> 06:47:26,460
the cigarette. Targeted ventilation sucked away the smoke before it reached me. That's the whole

4494
06:47:26,460 --> 06:47:34,380
point. Surely he were affected personally though. Surely. Ah, he nodded at the far end of shared

4495
06:47:34,380 --> 06:47:39,660
motor nerves, tail ops jiggled in sympathy. Changed the eyes to look at the world, changed the me

4496
06:47:39,660 --> 06:47:45,660
that does the looking. Something like that. Now he was watching me with fleshly eyes.

4497
06:47:45,660 --> 06:47:50,300
Across the membrane those snakes and eye stocks returned to their work on the virtual carcass,

4498
06:47:50,300 --> 06:47:55,740
as if deciding they wasted enough time on pointless distraction. I wondered which body he was in now.

4499
06:47:56,940 --> 06:48:02,460
I'm surprised you'd have to ask, the meat one said. Doesn't my body language tell you everything?

4500
06:48:02,460 --> 06:48:07,500
Aren't jargonauts supposed to read minds? He was right of course. I wasn't interested in

4501
06:48:07,500 --> 06:48:12,940
Cunningham's words. Those were just the carrier wave. He couldn't hear the real conversation we

4502
06:48:12,940 --> 06:48:18,220
were having. All his angles and services spoke volumes, and although their voices were strangely

4503
06:48:18,220 --> 06:48:22,940
fizzled with feedback and distortion, I knew I'd be able to understand them eventually. I only had

4504
06:48:22,940 --> 06:48:29,900
to keep him talking. But Yuka Sarasti chose that moment to wander past and surgically trash my best

4505
06:48:29,900 --> 06:48:36,540
laid plans. Ciri is the best in the field, he remarked, but not when it gets too close to home.

4506
06:48:39,900 --> 06:48:45,260
Why should man expect his prayer for mercy to be heard by what is above him when he shows no

4507
06:48:45,340 --> 06:48:49,500
mercy to what is under him? Pierre Trobetskoy.

4508
06:48:51,340 --> 06:48:57,980
The thing is, Chelsea said, this whole first person thing takes effort. You have to care

4509
06:48:57,980 --> 06:49:03,260
enough to try, you know? I've been working my ass off on this relationship. I've been working so

4510
06:49:03,260 --> 06:49:09,260
hard, but you just don't seem to care. She thought she was breaking the news. She thought I hadn't

4511
06:49:09,260 --> 06:49:15,020
