Cunningham zoomed the split-screen. The huddled scrambler had remained motionless,

4573
06:55:14,620 --> 06:55:18,460
except for the rippling of its cuticle and the undulation of its free arms.

4574
06:55:19,260 --> 06:55:24,620
But before, I'd only seen eight arms. Now I could make out the bony spur of a ninth from peaking

4575
06:55:24,620 --> 06:55:30,460
from behind the central mass. A ninth arm curled up and hidden from view, tick-tick-ticking while

4576
06:55:30,460 --> 06:55:36,060
another creature casually leaned against the other side of the wall. Now there was nothing.

4577
06:55:36,060 --> 06:55:39,740
The floating scrambler had drifted aimlessly back to the center of its enclosure.

4578
06:55:41,020 --> 06:55:43,820
James' eyes shone. We've got to check the rest of...

4579
06:55:44,780 --> 06:55:49,740
But Thesias had been watching and was way ahead of us. It had already searched the archives and

4580
06:55:49,740 --> 06:55:55,580
served up the results. Three similar exchanges over two days, ranging in duration from a tenth

4581
06:55:55,580 --> 06:56:03,420
of a second to almost two. They're talking, James said. Cunningham shrugged, a forgotten

4582
06:56:03,420 --> 06:56:09,020
cigarette burning down between his fingers. So do a lot of things, and at that rate of exchange,

4583
06:56:09,020 --> 06:56:13,820
