and golden ratios everywhere in nature, and there's no gene codes for them. It's all just mechanical

4712
07:08:58,700 --> 07:09:04,940
interactions. Take a developing embryo. The genes say start growing or stop growing, but the number

4713
07:09:04,940 --> 07:09:09,020
of digits in vertebrae result from the mechanics of cells bumping up against other cells.

4714
07:09:09,660 --> 07:09:15,020
Those mitotic spindles I mentioned? Absolutely essential for replication in every eukaryotic cell,

4715
07:09:15,020 --> 07:09:19,740
and they accrete like crystals without any genetic involvement. You'd be surprised how much of life

4716
